  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The computational model predicts absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are addressed; 7 are formally assessed and 6 are scoped out at MRL 5 due to epistemic constraints. The intended use scope — steady-state hemolysis index prediction at nominal VAD operating conditions (3500–6000 RPM, 4–8 L/min flow) for pre-market regulatory submission — is described in the Claim and Requirement bindings. Decision: Accepted under Minimal profile review.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-cfd-hemolysis-class3-vad",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-in-vitro-validation"
  ],
